obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (12527)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title and extent.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 14 of 2002, s. 2, for "Inter-State" (w.e.f. 28-3-2002).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_24_32_00003_195633_1517807321564&sectionId=12527&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_24_32_00003_195633_1517807321564
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the ^1[Inter-State River] Water Disputes Act,`
  line 1956.
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of India.`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (12528)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_24_32_00003_195633_1517807321564&sectionId=12528&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_24_32_00003_195633_1517807321564
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `(a) "prescribed" means prescribed by rules made under this Act;`
  line
  line `(b) "Tribunal" means a Water Disputes Tribunal constituted under section 4;`
  line
  line `(c) "water dispute" means any dispute or difference between two or more State Governments with`
  line `respect to--`
  line
  line `(i) the use, distribution or control of the waters of, or in, any inter-State river or river valley;`
  line or
  line
  line `(ii) the interpretation of the terms of any agreement relating to the use, distribution or control`
  line `of such waters or the implementation of such agreement; or`
  line
  line `(iii) the levy of any water rate in contravention of the prohibition contained in section 7.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (12529)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Complaints by State Governments as to water disputes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_24_32_00003_195633_1517807321564&sectionId=12529&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_24_32_00003_195633_1517807321564
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `If it appears to the Government of`
  line `any State that a water dispute with the Government of another State has arisen or is likely to arise by`
  line `reason of the fact that the interests of the State, or of any of the inhabitants thereof, in the waters of an`
  line `inter-State river or river valley have been, or are likely to be, affected prejudicially by--`
  line
  line `(a) any executive action or legislation taken or passed, or proposed to be taken or passed, by the`
  line `other State; or`
  line
  line `(b) the failure of the other State or any authority therein to exercise any of their powers with`
  line `respect to the use, distribution or control of such waters; or`
  line
  line `(c) the failure of the other State to implement the terms of any agreement relating to the use,`
  line `distribution or control of such waters,`
  line
  line `the State Government may, in such form and manner as may be prescribed, request the Central`
  line `Government to refer the water dispute to a Tribunal for adjudication.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (12530)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Constitution of Tribunal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_24_32_00003_195633_1517807321564&sectionId=12530&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_24_32_00003_195633_1517807321564
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1) When any request under section 3 is received from any State`
  line `Government in respect of any water dispute and the Central Government is of opinion that the water`
  line `dispute cannot be settled by negotiations, the Central Government shall, within a period not exceeding`
  line `one year from the date of receipt of such request, by notification in the Official Gazette, constitute a`
  line `Water Disputes Tribunal for the adjudication of the water dispute:`
  line
  line `Provided that any dispute settled by a Tribunal before the commencement of the Inter-State Water`
  line `Disputes (Amendment) Act, 2002 (14 of 2000) shall not be re-opened.]`
  line
  line ^2
  line `[(2) The Tribunal shall consist of a Chairman and two other members nominated in this behalf by the`
  line `Chief Justice of India from among persons who at the time of such nomination are Judges of the Supreme`
  line `Court or of a High Court.]`
  line
  line ^3
  line `[(3) The Central Government may, in consultation with the Tribunal, appoint two or more persons as`
  line `assessors to advise the Tribual in the proceedings before it.]`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 3, ibid., for sub-section (1) (w.e.f. 28-3-2002).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 35 of 1968, s. 2, for sub-section (2) (w.e.f. 22-8-1968).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 14 of 2002, s. 3, for sub-section (3) (w.e.f. 28-3-2002).`
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (12531)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Adjudication of water disputes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_24_32_00003_195633_1517807321564&sectionId=12531&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_24_32_00003_195633_1517807321564
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `(1) When a Tribunal has been constituted under section 4, the`
  line `Central Government shall, subject to the prohibition contained in section 8, refer the water disputes and`
  line `any matter appearing to be connected with, or relevant to, the water dispute to the Tribunal for`
  line adjudication.
  line
  line `^1[(2) The Tribunal shall investigate the matters referred to it and forward to the Central Government a`
  line `report setting out the facts as found by it and giving its decision on the mattes referred to it within a`
  line `period of three years:`
  line
  line `Provided that if the decision cannot be given for unavoidable reasons, within a period of three years,`
  line `the Central Government may extend the period for a further period not exceeding two years.`
  line
  line `(3) If,upon consideration of the decision of the Tribunal, the Central Government or any State`
  line `Government is of opinion that anything therein contained requires explanation or that guidance is needed`
  line `upon any point not originally referred to the Tribunal, the Central Government or the State Government,`
  line `as the case may be, within three months from the date of the decision, again refer the matter to the`
  line `Tribunal for further consideration, and on such reference, the Tribunal may forward to the Central`
  line `Government a further report within one year from the date of such reference giving such explanation or`
  line `guidance as it deems fit and in such a case, the decision of the Tribunal shall be deemed to be modified`
  line `accordingly:`
  line
  line `Provided that the period of one year within which the Tribunal may forward its report to the Central`
  line `Government may be extended by the Central Government, for such further period as it considers`
  line necessary.]
  line
  line `^2[(4) If the members of the Tribunal differ in opinion on any point, the point shall be decided`
  line `according to the opinion of the majority.]`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 4, ibid., for sub-section (2) (w.e.f. 28-3-2002).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 35 of 1968, s. 3 (w.e.f. 22-8-1968).`
obj_root_law_sections_5_a:
  sectionId (12532)
  sectionNo 5A
  orderNo 6
  title `Filling of vacancies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 4, ibid. (w.e.f. 22-8-1968).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_24_32_00003_195633_1517807321564&sectionId=12532&sectionno=5A&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_24_32_00003_195633_1517807321564
obj_root_law_sections_5_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[5A. Filling of vacancies.--If, for any reason a vacancy (other than a temporary absence) occurs in`
  line `the office of the Chairman or any other member of a Tribunal, such vacancy shall be filled by a person to`
  line `be nominated in this behalf by the Chief Justice of India in accordance with the provisions of sub-section`
  line `(2) of section 4, and the investigation of the matter referred to the Tribunal may be continued by the`
  line `Tribunal after the vacancy is filed and from the stage at which the vacancy occurred.]`
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (12533)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 7
  title `Publication of decision of Tribunal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_24_32_00003_195633_1517807321564&sectionId=12533&sectionno=6&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_24_32_00003_195633_1517807321564
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1)] The Central Government shall publish the decision`
  line `of the Tribunal in the Official Gazette and the decision shall be final and binding on the parties to the`
  line `dispute and shall be given effect to by them.`
  line
  line `^2[(2) The decision of the Tribunal, after its publication in the Official Gazette by the Central`
  line `Government under sub-section (1), shall have the same force as an order or decree of the Supreme Court.]`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Section 6 renumbered as sub-section (1) thereof by Act 14 of 2002, s. 5 (w.e.f. 28-3-2002).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by s. 5, ibid. (w.e.f. 28-3-2002).`
obj_root_law_sections_6_a:
  sectionId (12534)
  sectionNo 6A
  orderNo 8
  title `Power to make schemes to implement decision of Tribunal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_24_32_00003_195633_1517807321564&sectionId=12534&sectionno=6A&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_24_32_00003_195633_1517807321564
obj_root_law_sections_6_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[6A. Power to make schemes to implement decision of Tribunal.--(1) Without prejudice to the`
  line `provisions of section 6, the Central Government may, be notification in the Official Gazette, frame a`
  line `scheme or schemes whereby provision may be made for all matters necessary to give effect to the`
  line `decision of a Tribunal.`
  line
  line `(2) A scheme framed under sub-section (1) may provide for--`
  line
  line `(a) the establishment of any authority (whether described as such or as a committee or other`
  line `body) for the implementation of the decision or directions of the Tribunal;`
  line
  line `(b) the composition, jurisdiction, powers and functions of the authority, the term of office and`
  line `other conditions of service of, the procedure to be followed by, and the manner of filling vacancies`
  line `among, the members of the authority;`
  line
  line `^2[(ba) requisitioning of any data, as may be required by it.]`
  line
  line `(c) the holding of a minimum under of meetings of the authority every year, the quorum for such`
  line `meetings and the procedure thereat;`
  line
  line `(d) the appointment of any standing ad hoc or other committees by the authority;`
  line
  line `(e) the employment of a Secretary and other staff by the authority, the pay and allowances and`
  line `other conditions of service of such staff;`
  line
  line `(f) the constitution of a fund by the authority, the amounts that may be credited to such fund and`
  line `the expenses to which the fund may be applied;`
  line
  line `(g) the form and the manner in which accounts shall be kept by the authority;`
  line
  line `(h) the submission of an annual report by the authority of its activities;`
  line
  line `(i) the decisions of the authority which shall be subject to review;`
  line
  line `(j) the constitution of a committee for making such review and the procedure to be followed by`
  line `such committee; and`
  line
  line `(k) any other matter which may be necessary or proper for the effective implementation of the`
  line `decision or directions of the Tribunal.`
  line
  line `(3) In making provision in any scheme framed under sub-section (1) for the establishment of an`
  line `authority for giving effect to the decision of a Tribunal, the Central Government may, having regard to`
  line `the nature of the jurisdiction, powers and functions required to be vested in such authority in accordance`
  line `with such decision and all other relevant circumstances, declare in the said scheme that such authority`
  line `shall, under the name specified in the said schemes have capacity to acquire, hold and dispose of property,`
  line `enter into contracts, sue and be sued and do all such acts as may be necessary for the proper exercise and`
  line `discharge of its jurisdiction, powers and functions.`
  line
  line `(4) A scheme may empower the authority to make, with the previous approval of the Central`
  line `Government, regulations for giving effect to the purposes of the scheme.`
  line
  line `(5) The Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, add to, amend, or vary, any`
  line `scheme framed under sub-section (1).`
  line
  line `(6) Every Scheme framed under this section shall have effect not withstand anything contained in any`
  line `law for the time being in force (other than this Act) or any instrument having effect by virtue of any law`
  line `other than this Act.`
  line
  line `(7) Every scheme and every regulation made under a scheme shall be laid, as soon as may be after it`
  line `is made, before each House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days which`
  line `may be comprised in one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the`
  line `session immediately following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in`
  line `making any modification in the scheme or the regulation or both houses agree that the scheme or the`
  line `regulation should not be made, the scheme or the regulation shall thereafter have effect only in such`
  line `modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that any such modification or`
  line `annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done under that scheme or`
  line regulation.]
obj_root_law_sections_6_a_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 45 of 1980, s. 2 (w.e.f. 27-8-1980).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 14 of 2002, s. 6 (w.e.f. 28-3-2002).`
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (12535)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 9
  title `Prohibition of levy of seigniorage, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_24_32_00003_195633_1517807321564&sectionId=12535&sectionno=7&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_24_32_00003_195633_1517807321564
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `(1) No State Government shall, by reason only of the`
  line `fact that any works for the conservation, regulation or utilisation of water resources of an inter-State river`
  line `have been constructed within the limits of the State, impose, or authorise the imposition of, any`
  line `seigniorage or additional rate or fee (by whatever name called) in respect of the use of such water by any`
  line `other State or the inhabitants thereof.`
  line
  line `(2) Any dispute or difference between two or more State Governments with respect to the levy of any`
  line `water rate in contravention of the prohibition contained in sub-section (1) shall be deemed to be a water`
  line dispute.
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (12536)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 10
  title `Bar of reference of certain disputes to Tribunal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 36 of 1957, s. 2 and the Second Schedule, for "1955" (w.e.f. 17-9-1957)`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_24_32_00003_195633_1517807321564&sectionId=12536&sectionno=8&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_24_32_00003_195633_1517807321564
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in`
  line `section 3 or section 5, no reference shall be made to a Tribunal of any dispute that may arise regarding`
  line `any matter which may be referred to arbitration under the River Boards Act, ^1[1956].`
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (12537)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 11
  title `Powers of Tribunal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_24_32_00003_195633_1517807321564&sectionId=12537&sectionno=9&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_24_32_00003_195633_1517807321564
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Tribunal shall have the same powers as are vested in a civil court`
  line `under the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908), in respect of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) summoning and enforcing the attendance of any person and examining him on oath;`
  line
  line `(b) requiring the discovery and production of documents and material objects;`
  line
  line `^1[(ba) requisitioning of any data, as may be required by it;]`
  line
  line `(c) issuing commissions for the examination of witnesses or for local investigation;`
  line
  line `(d) any other matter which may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) The Tribunal may require any State Government to carry out, or permit to be carried out, such`
  line `surveys and investigation as may be considered necessary for the adjudication of any water dispute`
  line `pending before it.`
  line
  line `(3) A decision of the Tribunal may contain directions as to the Government by which the expenses of`
  line `the Tribunal and any costs incurred by any State Government in appearing before the Tribunal are to be`
  line `paid, and may fix the amount of any expenses or costs to be so paid, and so far as it relates to expense or`
  line `costs, may be enforced as if it were an order made by the Supreme Court.`
  line
  line `(4)`
  line `^2[Subject to the provisions of this act and any rules that may be made there under], the Tribunal`
  line `may, by order, regulate its practice and procedure.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins.by Act 14 of 2002, s. 6 (w.e.f. 28-3-2002).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 35 of 1968, s. 5, for "Subject to any rules that may be made under this Act" (w.e.f. 22-8-1968)`
obj_root_law_sections_9_a:
  sectionId (12538)
  sectionNo 9A
  orderNo 12
  title `maintenance of date bank and information.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 14 of 2002, s. 7 (w.e.f. 28-3-2002).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_24_32_00003_195633_1517807321564&sectionId=12538&sectionno=9A&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_24_32_00003_195633_1517807321564
obj_root_law_sections_9_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[9A. maintenance of date bank and information.--(1) The Central Government shall maintain a`
  line `data bank and information system at the national level for each river basin which shall include data`
  line `regarding water resources, land, agriculture, and matters relation thereto, as the Central Government may`
  line `prescribe form time to time. The State Government shall supply the date to the Central Government or to`
  line `an agency appointed by the Central Government for the purposes, as and when required.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government shall have powers to verify the data supplied by the State Government,`
  line `and appoint any person or persons for the purpose and take such measures as it may consider necessary.`
  line `The person or persons so appointed shall have the powers to summon such records and information from`
  line `the concerned State Government as are considered necessary to discharge their functions under this`
  line section.]
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (12539)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 13
  title `Allowances or fees for presiding officer of Tribunal and assessors.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 35 of 1968, s. 6, for "The presiding officer of a Tribunal" (w.e.f. 22-8-1968).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_24_32_00003_195633_1517807321564&sectionId=12539&sectionno=10&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_24_32_00003_195633_1517807321564
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `^1[The Chairman and`
  line `other members of a Tribunal] and the assessors shall be entitled to receive such remuneration, allowances`
  line `or fees as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (12540)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 14
  title `Bar of jurisdiction of Supreme Court and other courts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_24_32_00003_195633_1517807321564&sectionId=12540&sectionno=11&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_24_32_00003_195633_1517807321564
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained`
  line `in any other law, neither the Supreme Court nor any other Court shall have or exercise jurisdiction in`
  line `respect of any water dispute which may be referred to a Tribunal under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (12541)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 15
  title `Dissolution of Tribunal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_24_32_00003_195633_1517807321564&sectionId=12541&sectionno=12&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_24_32_00003_195633_1517807321564
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government shall dissolve the Tribunal after it has`
  line `forwarded its report and as soon as the Central Government is satisfied that no further reference to the`
  line `Tribunal in the matter would be necessary.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (12542)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 16
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_24_32_00003_195633_1517807321564&sectionId=12542&sectionno=13&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_24_32_00003_195633_1517807321564
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government, after consultation with the State`
  line `Governments, may, by notification in the Official Gazette, make rules to carry out the purposes of this`
  line Act.
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generally of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the form and manner in which complaint as to any water dispute may be made by any State`
  line Government;
  line
  line `(b) the matters in respect of which a Tribunal may be vested with the powers of a Civil Court;`
  line
  line `(c) the procedure to be followed by a Tribunal under this Act;`
  line
  line `(d) the remuneration, allowances or fees payable to ^1[the Chairman and other members] of a`
  line `Tribunal and assessors;`
  line
  line `^2[(e) the terms and conditions of service of officers and assessors of the Tribunal;]`
  line
  line `(f) any other matter which has to be, or may be, prescribed.`
  line
  line `^3[(3) Every rule made under this section shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before each`
  line `House of Parliament while it is in session for a total period of thirty days,`
  line `^4[which may be comprised in`
  line `one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session immediately`
  line `following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid] both Houses agree in making any modification`
  line `in the rule of both Houses agree that the rule should not be made, the rule shall thereafter have effect only`
  line `in the modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be, so, however, that any such modification or`
  line `annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done under that rule.]`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 35 of 1968, s. 7, for "the presiding officer" (w.e.f. 22-8-1968).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 14 of 2002, s. 8, for clause (e) (w.e.f. 28-3-2002).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 35 of 1968, s. 7, for sub-section (3) (w.e.f. 22-8-1968).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 45 of 1980, s. 3, for certain words (w.e.f. 27-9-1980).`
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (12543)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 17
  title `Constitution of Ravi and Beas Waters Tribunal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 20 of 1986, s. 2 (w.e.f. 2-4-1986).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_24_32_00003_195633_1517807321564&sectionId=12543&sectionno=14&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_24_32_00003_195633_1517807321564
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `^1[14. Constitution of Ravi and Beas Waters Tribunal.--(1) Notwithstanding anything contained in`
  line `in the foregoing provisions of this Act, the Central Government may, by notification in the Official`
  line `Gazette, a constitute a Tribunal under this Act, to be known as the Ravi and Beas Waters Tribunal for the`
  line `verification and adjudication of the matters referred to in paragraphs 9.1 and 9.2, respectively, of the`
  line `Punjab Settlement.`
  line
  line `(2) When a Tribunal has been constituted under sub-section (1), the provisions of sub-sections (2) and`
  line `(3) of section 4, sub-sections (2), (3) and (4) of section 5 and sections 5A to 13 (both inclusive ) of this`
  line `Act relating to the constitution, jurisdiction, powers, authority and bar or jurisdiction shall, so far as may`
  line `be, but subject to sub-section (3) hereof, apply to the constitution, jurisdiction, powers, authority and bar`
  line `of jurisdiction in relation to the Tribunal constituted under sub-section (1).`
  line
  line `(3) When a Tribunal has been constituted under sub-section (1), the Central Government alone may`
  line `suo motu or at the request of the concerned State Government refer the mattes specified in paragraphs 9.1`
  line `and 9.2 of the Punjab Settlement to such Tribunal.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section, "Punjab Settlement" means the Memorandum of`
  line `Settlement signed at New Delhi on the 24th day of July, 1985.]`
